caption: Delicious chicago style pizza. Super friendly staff and great food.

Ordered delivery while staying downtown. It took about an hour which was fine and makes sense with a deep dish pizza. It wasn't hot when it arrived, which made it easy to eat like a traditional pizza but perhaps dining in is best. I appreciate they included plates, silverware, parmesian cheese and red hot pepper flakes but just didn't love the pizza. Got a medium Malnati Chicago Classic... comes with plenty of sausage on top, and cheese. Crust was a little hard and saltiness cracker like. Two people will be full with a medium, had extra for the morning.

Giving this 5 star because I really enjoyed my time here- I got the lunch special “Lou” which I really liked. It has spinach, mushrooms, tomatoes with mozzarella and cheddar cheese blend on garlicy crust. It was a cold day and snowing, so I picked the minestrone soup. We sat outside (there is outdoor covered area) following the social distancing rules. It was a great experience. I have no pictures because I gobbled that thing before I realized I didn’t take any picture ha!

DO NOT LISTEN TO THE TOURISTS! This place is bottom barrel for quality and stays open off the name. If you must have Chicago style pizza there are many other places that don't take advantage of you and will give you a edible pie. Worst Pizza in Chicago.

This was the very first location we ate at on our trip to Chicago, and let me tell you, I rejoiced where I live in Phoenix, AZ when they opened the same chain where I live. Best pizza outside of NYC and WELL worth the wait! GOOD THINGS COME TO THOSE WHO WAIT!!
The thin crust pizza was not good! They threw all my jalapeños on one slice of pizza, then forgot my toppings. When I called them they put me on hold for 20 minutes and never answered!!!!
I give you permission to load up on carbs and sugar!! Chicago deep dish is an absolute must experience and Lou Malnati’s was the perfect way to end our amazing trip to the Windy City.

Great food and service.

The pizza was ok, not my favorite deep dish. Service was decent, however we were done eating our pizza before our appetizer even arrived. That being said, the garlic cheese bread appetizer was absolutely fantastic.

What is there not to love about Lou Malnati's? If you are not from Chicago I highly recommend you to go here and eat pizza. You will not be disappointed and not leave hungry! You cannot go wrong with ordering the deep dish pizza. Yes there is a lot of other pizzeras around but Lou's is where it's at.
Best pizza ever.

I really like it.

Deep dish pizza is low on the totem pole in terms of pizza style--pan is the best, don't @ me--yet pizza is pizza so you're gonna have a good time. Staff was very friendly. Our waiter was weirdly disappointed that we needed a to-go box.

The pizza was delicious, but we had to wait about two hours to get it. An hour in the lobby and another hour at our table. We even pre-ordered our food. Oh well. It was a Saturday night after all.  But when the pizza finally came it was outstanding. So satisfying! The staff in the lobby was friendly, and the wait staff at our table was excellent. Super friendly and attentive.

This place was great! There was a wait, which seems to be normal, but the waitstaff were all so kind and helpful. The staff at the top floor all recommended we head downstairs and preorder our pizza, so we wouldn't have to wait so long for our pizza to come out. We did that, and it felt like in no time we were sitting down and ready to eat. We got appetizers and a drink and within a few minutes after that we got our pizza. The pizza was so good, super cheesy and the crust was delicious. The sauce was good and was perfectly balanced with the cheese. I highly recommend coming here for a traditional chicago deep dish.
Deep dish mmmmmmmm

Loved it! I was visiting Chicago for a couple days from India for work, and happened to visit the place. Although the wait time was quite a lot (45 mins outside and 45 more while seated), it felt worth it. The taste was good, service too. Enjoyable. Only negative was the wait time.
Amazing pizza, the sauce is sooo good. We had a great waiter, and the decor is very cool. Highly recommend!

Definitely recommend this place, worth the trip to Chicago alone.

So disappointing. I rarely write reviews because I honestly never receive service this horrible. We waited 1 and a half hours to get seated, no problem, it was busy and understandable. Once seated, someone came and taped our pre-order slip on the stand on our table. Then absolutely no one came for 10 minutes...WE had to flag someone down to ask for a bar menu and for waters. We then ordered a can of white claw and no one came with the waters or drink for another 20 minutes. That is 30 minutes of waiting, after 1.5 hours, with a “pre-order” that was supposed to make the food come out faster. We were so upset and flagged down the waitress we originally had. As I was explaining what happened, she said “well your pizza is here already and I’ll see about the drink”. It felt dismissive and she did not address the service so far. The pizza was LUKEWARM and the drink (a can, not cocktail)came out after another 5 minutes. The cheese was no longer melted and the “butter crust” got hard and tough so fast. I believe that Lou’s has good pizza, and other locations may be better but we had an absolutely horrid experience and introduction to the restaurant. Super sad.

I can’t understand why this is such a loved place. I didn’t know I could have called ahead, my bad! We were told it was about a 30 minute wait, not even close it was exactly 60 minutes.  They told use we could order our pizza and appetizer while we were waiting. The hostess stand said the kitchen would time everything if we ordered both ahead. My husband went to order ahead and was only able to order the pizza, no appetizers. Luckily when he was ordering ahead he noticed my phone number had been put in wrong. Had the hostess verified the phone number I could have corrected the 2 turned around numbers right away (dyslexia?).  When we were seated we ordered drinks and some cheesy bread. The pizza came out about 2 minutes after the cheesy bread. My glass of wine came out about 5 minutes after the pizza. My husband and daughter got the sausage pizza they said was good and the crust was cooked. I got the vegetable pizza and the crust was cooked, but mushy. After we ate we were rushed out right away so they could have the table. We wanted some desert, so we got a single tiramisu to go.  They really should consider reservation only or seating times and only a small area for walk-ins. Then give the walk-ins an accurate wait time. I was really disappointed, can’t believe it’s one of my best friends favorite restaurants.

Plenty of seating. Excellent service. Pizza takes at least 30 min to cook, but is worth the wait. Lou's special pizza was yummy, but I wished I got plain cheese or chicken sausage instead - maybe next time I'm in Chicago!

As a New Yorker, this was my first time having deep dish, and it was amazing. Perfect sausage in every bite of their classic chicago pizza. Don't just take it from me, the pizza was so great that I even saw folks in the row in front on my flight back carry a box of their pizza with them. Expect to wait a little bit for the pizza, but it's well worth it, and I'll be going back.

This was our first deep dish pizza on our first trip to Chicago, and we loved it! Our server Jonathan S. had great recommendations, very friendly and helpful. There was a 1 hour wait, but it was exactly what they told us it would be. We signed up for the text list in person; this was very accurate and allowed us to walk and shop Michigan Ave while we waited. We got a link so we were able to track our place in line and time out our return. Great location, great staff, loved this experience!
